# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore — tells Docker what NOT to copy into the container.
#
# Think of it like .gitignore but for Docker builds.
# Excluding these makes the build faster and the image smaller.
# Docker doesn't need your local node_modules — it installs fresh ones inside.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Local dependency folders — Docker installs these fresh inside the container
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Built output — Docker rebuilds these from source
**/dist
**/build
**/.turbo

# Environment files — NEVER bake secrets into a Docker image.
# Set these as environment variables in Railway's dashboard instead.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!artifacts/everydayai/.env.production

# Editor and OS noise
.vscode
.idea
*.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Git history — not needed at runtime
.git
.gitignore

# Replit-specific files
.replit
replit.nix
.local
.upm

# Logs
*.log
logs/

# Test files
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts
**/__tests__

# Docs (not needed in production)
*.md
!README.md
